ZCZC GE69
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 252300 UTC
AT THE START OF THE PERIOD AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE
CENTRED OVER EERN EUROPE WILL EXTEND A RIDGE WWARDS
ACROSS THE SERN N SEA AND THE SERN BRITISH ISLES. AT THE
SAME TIME AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 985 IS EXP E OF
ICELAND. THROUGH SUNDAY THIS LOW WILL RUN E TO BECOME
SLOW MOV OFF WERN SCANDINAVIA. FURTHER SHALLOWER LOWS
ARE EXP TO AFFECT THE AREA AROUND ICELAND. MEANWHILE THE
HIGH OVER EERN EUROPE WILL GRADUALLY EXTEND ITS
INFLUENCE SUCH THAT BY TUESDAY IT IS LIKELY TO AFFECT
THE WHOLE OF THE N SEA AND MUCH OF THE WATERS SURROUNDING
THE BRITISH ISLES. WITH THIS SET UP STRG WINDS WILL BE
CONFINED TO AREAS N OF 55 N. IN PARTICULAR EARLY IN THE
PERIOD WITH GALES AT FIRST IN VIKING FAIR ISLE. WINDS
SHOULD MOD ACROSS ALL PARTS BY MONDAY AND REMAIN LIGHT
INTO TUESDAY
